OL,6,FThis all adds to the argument that
OL,7,Freports of the death of Freeview are
OL,8,Fgreatly overstated. Clearly there are
OL,9,Fstill imperatives to improve the
OL,10,Fservice.
OL,12,FOf course, it will be interesting to
OL,13,Fsee how the Freely service takes off.
OL,14,FClearly there are advantages to moving
OL,15,Fto an internet delivery model.
OL,17,FMy argument has always been that
OL,18,Fmaintaining the basic Freeview service
OL,19,Fwill be necessary for a long time `
OL,20,Fboth for resilience and potentially
OL,21,Fvulnerable consumers.
